The paper focuses on facial expression analysis and restoration using generative adversarial networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method also involves region relation modeling and facial action units detection, which can be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of facial expression analysis in the wild, which can be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
